      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: forward pending timeout snapshot in waitForAgentJob fallback timer",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n- When a sub-agent run was force-killed by its run timeout, the parent session never received the timeout completion event. The sub-agent registry correctly recorded `status: \"timeout\"`, but `agent.wait` downgraded it to a generic `gateway_draining`/`queue` timeout, losing the real hard-timeout phase (`preflight`/`provider`/`post_turn`).\n- Root cause: `waitForAgentJob`'s outer timer callback only consulted `getPendingAgentRunError` and ignored `getPendingAgentRunTimeout`. When a pending timeout was registered without a pending error, the timer called `finish(null)`, discarding the timeout snapshot.\n- Fix: Make the wait-timer fallback symmetric — when no pending error exists, consult `getPendingAgentRunTimeout` and forward the snapshot for hard timeout phases only. Soft phases (`queue`, `gateway_draining`) remain correctable via the retry grace timer.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**E2E proof (all three hard-timeout phases):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/agent-job.subagent-timeout-notify.e2e.test.ts --run\n ✓ subagent hard-timeout parent notification (#89095) > forwards the preflight hard-timeout\n ✓ subagent hard-timeout parent notification (#89095) > forwards the provider hard-timeout\n ✓ subagent hard-timeout parent notification (#89095) > forwards the post_turn hard-timeout\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  3 passed (3)\n```\n\n**Regression guard (server-methods unit tests):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  161 passed (161)\n```\n\n**Agent outcome contract:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/agent-run-terminal-outcome.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  14 passed (14)\n```",
